Boeing, Dow Inc. share losses lead Dow's 1,263-point drop

Behind declines for shares of Boeing and Dow Inc., the Dow Jones Industrial Average is slumping Wednesday afternoon. Shares of Boeing BA, +0.10% and Dow Inc. DOW, +2.36% are contributing to the index's intraday decline, as the Dow DJIA, +0.52% was most recently trading 1,263 points (5.0%) lower. Boeing's shares have fallen $32.28 (14.0%) while those of Dow Inc. are down $2.71 (8.6%), combining for a roughly 237-point drag on the Dow. Other components contributing significantly to the decline include United Technologies UTX, American Express AXP, -0.57%, and Pfizer PFE, -0.48%. A $1 move in any of the index's 30 components results in a 6.78-point swing.

